JOHANNESBURG - Black Friday sales boosted retail sales by 8.2 percent in November, outstripping forecasts. According to data released by Stats SA on Wednesday, economists expected growth to improve only by 3.7 percent. November’s total retail sales amounted to R94.67-billion. IN TWEETS: Hilarious #BlackFridayDosandDonts Sales of household furniture, appliances and equipment were among the highest contributors to the figure. eNCA